  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "/DpUmsKs5aKpVtdE2/FvYF310tE=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# arrays in state schemas must use mandatory notation\n\nIn GraphQL state schemas, arrays follow a strict convention:\n\n```graphql\ntype ServiceOfferingState {\n    tiers: [Tier!]!        # \u2705 Correct \u2014 both inner and outer are required\n    items: [Item]           # \u274c Wrong \u2014 must use [Item!]!\n}\n```\n\nObjects inside arrays must include an `OID!` field for unique identification:\n\n```graphql\ntype Tier {\n    id: OID!               # Required for array items\n    name: String\n    label: OLabel          # Optional but useful for metadata\n}\n```\n\nThe `OID!` field enables operations to target specific items within arrays (e.g., \"update the tier with this ID\"). Without it, there is no stable way to reference individual array elements across operations.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[schema design]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z"
    }
  },
